This paper is primarily focused on the statistical and information theoretic characteristics of deep network representations, which is a core topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the application of these characteristics in computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper investigates mutual information, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
